Western Cape Premier Alan Winde speaks to eNCA to discuss the situation in the province.Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC in the Western Cape wants the province to revert to level 5 lockdown. The province has recorded nearly 4,500 COVID-19 infections. READ: COVID-19: SA cases rise to 8895, death toll at 178 It's followed by Gauteng with below two thousand infections. The Western Cape has also recorded the highest number of deaths, currently at 88. READ: Mass COVID-19 testing drive held in Diepsloot The ANC in the province says a large number of people are exposed to infections at shopping centres, farms and factories. It's also calling for law enforcement to be deployed at hotspots. Meanwhile, Western Cape Premier Alan Winde wants President Cyril Ramaphosa's intervention to ease backlogs in COVID-19 test results. Watch the full interview with Western Cape Premier Alan Winde in the video above. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.